title: Citrix: Session Count
agents: windows
catalog: app/citrix
license: GPLv2
distribution: citrix_session_detail
description:
 This check monitors Citrix XenApp/XenDesktop sessions on individual
 Citrix servers via piggyback data from the Delivery Controller.

 It reports the number of {Active} and {Disconnected} sessions per server
 and the age of the oldest disconnected session.

 The check returns {WARN} or {CRIT} if the number of active sessions
 exceeds configurable upper levels.

 The check returns {WARN} or {CRIT} if the number of disconnected sessions
 exceeds configurable upper levels.

 The check returns {WARN} or {CRIT} if the oldest disconnected session
 age exceeds configurable upper levels (default: 1 day / 3 days).

 Detailed information about individual disconnected sessions (username,
 idle duration) is available in the service details view.

 Requires the Citrix Session Detail agent plugin running on a
 Citrix Delivery Controller with the Citrix.Broker.Admin PowerShell snap-in.

discovery:
 One service is created per Citrix server (via piggyback).
